simula-an algol-based simulation language.wthis paper is an introduction to simula, aprogramming language designed to provide a systems analyst with unified concepts which facilitate theconcise description of discrete event systems.  a system description also serves as a source language simulationprogram.  simula is an extension of algol  in which the most important new conceptsis that of quasi-parallel processing.cacm september, dahl, o. j.nygaard, k.ca jb march ,   : pm